title: Ukraine Three Months Interbank Rate
description: Ukraine Three Months Interbank Rate was at 11.31 percent on Tuesday November 8. Interbank Rate in Ukraine averaged 14.07 percent from 2001 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 32.16 percent in March of 2009 and a record low of 3.59 percent in August of 2010. In Ukraine, the interbank rate is the rate of interest charged on short-term loans made between banks. This page provides - Ukraine Interbank Rate - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: National Bank of Ukraine
